The paper deals with the computational complexity of strategy improvement algorithms for solving graph-based infinite games, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The specific types of games studied in the paper include parity games (cs.DS), mean-payoff games (cs.AI), discounted-payoff games and simple stochastic games (cs.LO). Therefore, these sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
